summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of Seventy-five ($75.00) Dollars out of the general fund of the City of Seattle, to pay the claim of Ed. Hahn for damages to a horse, harness and wagon belonging to said Hahn, said damages being the result of a collision with a runaway team of the Street Department on the 22nd day of June, 1916, on Railroad Avenue, near Hanford Street in the City of Seattle, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
